pageContext.claim: “I saluted 1,106 cadets, and that’s not easy. Even the general said, That’s amazing. Other presidents would never have been able to do it. Because usually they do the first 10. They do 10 honor rolls, and then they go home. I stayed there for hours.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump saluted the cadets in pairs. Trump has previously falsely said no other president shook all of the hands at Annapolis, and once again he makes a similar claim here. Video shows Obama shook every hand at West Point.
